cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with developing support vector algorithms for optimizing performance measures in machine learning. It also involves optimization techniques and the use of cutting plane solvers, which are commonly used in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the partial AUC is often used as a performance measure in image classification tasks. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as machine learning is a subfield of AI. 

The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). However, these categories are less likely as the focus of the paper is on machine learning and performance measures.
